{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "AB231", "title": "Income and corporation taxes: credits: work opportunity credit.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["Incomeandcorporationtaxes", "credits", "workopportunitycredit"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "The Personal Income Tax Law and the Corporation Tax Law allow various credits against the taxes imposed by those laws.\n\nThis bill, for taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2026, and before January 1, 2031, would allow a credit against those taxes to a qualified taxpayer in an amount equal to 40% of the qualified wages paid or incurred to a qualified employee employed during the taxable year. The bill would define a qualified employee for this purpose to mean an individual that, among other things, has been convicted of a felony, as provided, and has a hiring date not more than one year after the date the individual was convicted or was released from prison.\n\nExisting law requires any bill authorizing a new tax expenditure to contain, among other things, specific goals that the tax expenditure will achieve, detailed performance indicators, and data collection requirements. \n\nThis bill would include additional information required for any bill authorizing a new income tax expenditure.\n\nThis bill would take effect immediately as a tax levy."}], "other_titles": [], "other_identifiers": [], "actions": [{"description": "Read first time. To print.", "date": "2025-01-13", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be heard in committee February 13.", "date": "2025-01-14", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Com. on REV. & TAX.", "date": "2025-02-10", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification":